title: No. 22 UNI knocks off No. 6 South Dakota State
text:
No. 22 UNI knocks off No. 6 South Dakota State No. 22 UNI knocks off No. 6 South Dakota State Panthers earn first conference win, stay in playoff hunt Video Photos Northern Iowa Panthers quarterback Aaron Bailey (15) runs with the ball during the second half of their NCAA football game at Hancock Stadium in Normal, Ill. on Saturday, Oct. 3, 2015. (Stephen Mally/The Gazette) Most Popular The Gazette October 24, 2015 | 11:30 pm 
Putting one in the win column was a major lift for No. 22 Northern Iowa, which upset No. 6 South Dakota State, 10-7, on Saturday afternoon at Coughlin-Alumni Stadium in Brookings, S.D. 
The win ended a 3-game losing streak for the Panthers (3-4, 1-3 MVFC) and kept them in the hunt for a playoff spot at the end of the season. 
Neither team was able to get much going until the Panthers drove 92 yards for a 24-yard field goal by Michael Schmadeke right before halftime. 
The Jackrabbits (5-2, 2-2) took the lead in the third quarter on a 6-yard pass from Taryn Christion to Connor Landberg, but the Panthers responded with a 35-yard TD run by quarterback Aaron Bailey on their next possession. 
Bailey started the game and finished with a team-high 169 rushing yards to go with 113 yards passing. Tyvis Smith had 54 rushing yards on 12 carries. 
UNI was tough on defense, piling up five sacks — three by defensive tackle Karter Schult — and 12 tackles for loss. 
SDSU had just 95 yards rushing on 37 attempts. 
The Jackrabbits had the ball at the UNI 11-yard line with 1:31 remaining, but the Panthers got the stop on fourth-and-one to preserve the win. It was UNI’s 19th win over a top 10 team since 2001. Your Next College Football Articles
